review_title: I am enjoying my new laptop!
review_text: It was time for me to purchase a new computer because my old desktop can't update to Windows 11.  I have always owned Dell laptop and computers, so it was a no brainer to purchase from Dell again.  The price was great making it a good time to purchase now.  The storage and memory are more than enough for me.  I do everyday activities, as well as watching videos and listening to music.  I'm loving it.  I would recommend this little gem.

review_text: Great product, decent price. The only negative I have about this product is the screen is dull, and the keyboard is loud. I'm not using this computer for streaming or too many videos so I do not mind the screen as it is good. I'm just spoiled by specialty screens in other devices i use for watching videos or streaming. The keyboard is very loud though. Other than those two minor things. This is a great computer for everyday use, and productivity. I would buy again

review_text: For more than 35 years all my pcs and laptops have been Dells, and in that time I can say unequivocally I have never had one problem and for that reason I have always relied on Dell for my computing needs. This is the third Inspiron 3530 I've purchased, one for me, the wife and my daughter. My first 15" Dell laptop is over 20 years old and still though limited by today's standards still works flawlessly. You take care of your Dell and Dell will take care of you.

review_title: 15 3530 - Great Performing Laptop For Everyday Use
review_text:
Laptop was purchased for daily home use and to complete an academic course. The 15.6" screen is useful when looking at drawings/diagrams and the keyboard with a numeric pad is extremely useful.

The SSD results in a snappy feeling response and quiet operation. Boot up times are in seconds and the laptop performs admirably with it's 13th Generation Intel I5. 

For the majority of the time, this laptop is running nothing more strenuous than MS Office, but it's interesting to note the 16gb of ddr4 ram does afford this machine the ability to run some pretty heavyweight pieces of software for content creators.

This laptop sits in a nice middle ground of capable without costing a fortune. It also looks really nice and whilst packing a large screen (by modern laptop standards), remains slim and portable enough for people on the move.

This is our second laptop from Dell, our previous being a 2 in 1 with a smaller OLED touch screen used for video editing and flight controller configuration. Both are great laptops.

No complaints so far with either machine. I would highly recommend Dell - great website, super clear pages, easy to order and very prompt delivery. 10/10 experience. You literally can't go wrong. Plenty of options along the way to ensure you land with the right machine for you. You can even spread the cost.

Thank you Dell.

Injured it, so far, your response for initial shipping and return has been speedy. I am patiently waiting for my newly repaired laptop. So far am satisfied wth Dell.

Fast, smooth from app to app, great product!   i have always been a Dell girl, they make a product you can count on!

Bought a Dell Inspiron "15" laptop after much research. I've had Dell in the past and never had any problems with them. The one I've just purchased is silver, slim and simple to use. Very user friendly. The whole process was easy, apart from the huge selection of laptops that made it difficult to choose. 
I've used this laptop for about 4 months now. The Intel i7 processor is fantastically fast and the graphics are amazing. I'll continue to use and recommend Dell.

Don't like:
   1) Power button - should be separate from the keyboard keys.

Overall though - no problems with the hardware after a month of use...

review_text: Recently picked up a new Inspiron 15 on a boxing day sale for a great price. Our current laptop is a 4 year old  Inspiron 15 (which still runs great) but is shared with my recently retired wife so we decided to get a new laptop (keeping the old one). The new laptop arrived quicker than I expected and was easy to setup, works great so far. It's perfect for my needs which includes some light gaming, web browsing and some office applications like Excel and Access. It's pretty light so good for on my lap and I like the keyboard (black with back light). Battery could be better but good enough. I purchased the 2 year warranty, I had the 3 year on my previous laptop but never used it. Only thing I don't know is longevity but my previous Dell's have worked out fine.

My partner has just got it back from a friend, also computer buff,  who managed to access his old laptop and transfer contents over. He was well impressed with this laptop and told my partner so. My partner is looking forward to using it. Thank you very much for excellent service and what appears to be an excellent product.

review_title: Always great computers and great service
review_text: I have had many Dells both at home and work since about 1990.  They've always been excellent machines and they don't load them down with all the junk store-bought PCs have. Only one time years ago did I have a problem with a certain model laptop.  The couple times over all the years that I needed service or technical support they were great and fast to resolve the problem.  This time I bought both a laptop and desktop at the same time and know I'll get the great service I've always received.

review_text:
I recently purchased the Dell Inspiron 15 laptop, and I couldn't be happier with my decision. It offers a perfect balance of performance and affordability, making it a fantastic choice for both personal and professional use.  

The laptop handles multitasking , The battery life is decent, lasting several hours on a single charge, and the display is crisp with vibrant colors.

I also appreciate how lightweight and portable it is for a 15-inch model, making it easy to carry around. the keyboard is comfortable to use for extended periods.

Overall, I would definitely buy this product again! Highly recommend it to anyone looking for a dependable and well-rounded laptop.

review_text: I love my new Inspiron 15. It has a fast 13th Gen i7 processor, lots of high speed memory, and great graphics. I will mostly use my laptop for gaming. I like Dell's reliability. My 2 older Dell laptops never gave me any trouble. My new Inspiron has the memory capacity and CPU speed that I want. It has a cool look and a sleek design. I highly recommend this Inspiron 3530 for anyone who wants a very capable laptop at a good price.

review_text: I have been using dell laptops and desktops since late 80's, when there were DOS and windows 3.1. 95, 98 etc. operation systems. I have experienced more than 9 different Dell models, and this is probably the fastest in terms of downloading, sending data in terms of speed. I have always preferred pro version of Windows. The laptop, Inspiron, is light in weight and boots up very quickly. I have not noticed any delay for all the work I do on it. My only criticism would be the lack of USB ports.

Would be nice to just start things up and have them work with minimal setup. Makes you think about Apple.

review_text: When I needed a new laptop, I automatically went to Dell.I had had 3 Dells previously and had always found them to be reliable and Dell's customer support to be quite good. I ordered by phone after doing some research. I purchased the Inspiron 15. The sales agent was most helpful, clearly answered my questions, acted most professionally without any upselling pressure. The laptop arrived in just a few days. The remote transfer of apps, documents and data files from the old laptop to the new one was quite easy. After the transfer, I was fully using the new laptop in just a few hours.

review_text:
I was looking for a Windows 11 laptop that was well specified, with a fast processor (Intel or AMD 7), plenty of memory and at least 512GB of hard drive, full HD 15" screen. All for a reasonable price. And I prefer silver to black, another consideration.
For less than I'd expected to pay, I was able to get 1TB of hard drive.
Arrived when I expected, in perfect condition.
In use, it's everything I wanted! WiFi and Bluetooth work seamlessly. Everything is very fast - downloads, updates, opening and closing files, start-up and shutdown.
It has an SD card slot, and I've found that transfer on and off SD card is faster than I have previously experienced.
Although it feels solid and well made, it's very light and easy to carry. I use it mainly at home, plugged in, but so far battery life when not connected is very finy, even when set for best performance.
Runs very quietly, doesn't get very hot even after a couple of hours. I didn't need a backlit keyboard, but I've got used to it and find that I like having it.

My husband is using the new laptop as a 2nd purchase for personal use.

review_text: Bought this about 2 weeks ago. For my needs which are forcussed on home management, money management and some fairly intense spreadsheets, it's fast and reliable. It came with the expected bloat which doesn't interfere with its use. The keyboard is very tactile and less prone to missed strokes plus it's backlit which I never thought important until I used a Lenovo laptop that had the feature. The fingerprint reader is a nice feature that allows easy login. The metal case provides a firm feel that makes working with the machine seem all that more reliable. I'm very happy with my purchase of this laptop.

I highly recommend this laptop.
